1
00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:06,000
Revision 1 is the governed baseline.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:11,500
A plain-language correction creates immutable revision 2, preserving its parent.

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:17,000
The child is verified independently. Trust is never inherited.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:22,500
A second correction creates revision 3 without erasing revision 2.

5
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:33,000
Revision 3 returns to compiled, reopening verification with lineage, policy delta, and proof state visible.
